==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inaccuracy
<hw>In*ac"cu*ra*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Inaccuracies</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of being inaccurate; lack of accuracy or
exactness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is inaccurate or incorrect; mistake;
fault; defect; error; <as>as, in <ex>inaccuracy</ex> in speech, copying,
calculation, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inaccurate</ent>⟦br⟧
